concept.title: SNMP Trap OIDs

othermeta.name: shortdesc
othermeta.content: List and description of digital SNMP values and OIDs exposed by the network management card for monitoring and alarm handling.

othermeta.name: entities
othermeta.content: snmp agent; oids; digital inputs; network management card AP9635; trap destinations; monitoring system

section.p: Any active traps can be view from a management information base (MIB) browser with correctly configured trap receiver connected to the NMC.
The following table shows the different traps that can be sent out from the NMC when triggered. The NMC will only send out the traps that are currently triggered in the system.
section.note: Base OID Address for APC / Reality: 1.3.6.1.4.1.318.
